Heh you define difficult and average much differently than i.  Ice spear is available.  Sunstrike is very rare, still fetching 50-100K and my server, despite being from the Kunark expansion, it never has trickled down sufficiently.  EER is never up for sale at all and requires a guild that can take down the Luclin ubers which aren't a walk in the park for most guilds, and GSS being an Emp Srra only drop requires a very powerful guild and is also never up for sale.  The average wizard (not the average uberguild wizard, but the average wizard) will have only ice spear, and if they are real lucky, sunstrike, although most aren't that lucky.  The average wizard will never see EER or GSS.  For GSS, that is partially justifiable since it is an upgrade to sunstrike, and maybe could be grouped with the ancient spells as you do.  However i think the solution i put forth only drops the difficulty of each of these spells by one notch, and still doesn't compare to having a 2K on a vendor.<br>
<br>
In short, sunstrike should be questable ala protection of the cabbage, EER should drop off those mobs that now drop moonfire, and GSS off those mobs that now drop EER, in addition to the Emp Ssra drop.  Work is still required to gain any of them, but the average wizard would be assured of ice and fire nukes at the least, with a good chance to get the magic based EER, and a slim chance to obtain the GSS sunstrike upgrade.  The ancient spells would remain unchanged.  Is that really so much to ask? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2002<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/6/03 4:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GM response on GSS and EER</span><hr size=1> The question I have to ask is, why don't we just put all spells on vendors then? Some spell drops are always going to be too hard for someone to get and any level you set is going to be arbitrary. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
