<br>
Look, part of my reasoning is that wizard class balance is based upon being the best nuker is any resist situation.  Only 1 out of 4 of wizard nukes being available means only one resist type is available unless you drop back to those old 50s draught spells.  And that's not only no fun, but effects our balance if we are forced to nuke with 50's spells.<br>
<br>
50% of those spells (now, 2 resist types) being available is more acceptable for the average wizard, since it is likely that something that's resistant to ice will be vulnerable to fire.  Lowering EER one step furthers this, allowing the magic nuke to be a bit more common, while not diluting it too much, and it isn't usually neccesary to have 3 resist types on hand, it's a luxury.  <br>
<br>
Lowering GSS one notch wno't make it THAT much more common, only about as common as EER is now.  The status symbol quality of the spells would even be maintained since they would still be earned spells not simple vendor spells, and ubers would of course have higher status options available like the ancient spells and the PoP big bangs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2006<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/6/03 6:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GM response on GSS and EER</span><hr size=1> &gt;No idea. But i bet it's more available than GSS.<br>
<br>
Actually, given that there wasn't one, it would be quite difficult to see that.<br>
<br>
&gt;Look, part of my reasoning is that wizard class balance is based upon being the best nuker is any resist situation. Only 1 out of 4 of wizard nukes being available means only one resist type is available unless you drop back to those old 50s draught spells. And that's not only no fun, but effects our balance if we are forced to nuke with 50's spells.<br>
<br>
Actually, that is pretty much the case anyways, even if you have to go back to late 50 spells.<br>
<br>
I am still trying to see what problem this is supposed to solve other than 'I don't have a full spellbook'. The simplest way to resolve what you are talking about would be to simply make SS drop a little bit more and leave the other 2 alone, so why wouldn't that work? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
