Cute, and your point is?  Moonfire is nevertheless a very powerful spell for a class who's balance is based only partly on their nukes, and i'm comparing spells from Luclin with other spells from Luclin.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Actually, that is pretty much the case anyways, even if you have to go back to late 50 spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Like i said, being forced to go back to 50's spells is &quot;not only no fun, but effects our balance if we are forced to nuke with 50's spells&quot; because it basically reduces us to the same effectiveness as a 50s wizard, resist rates aside.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I am still trying to see what problem this is supposed to solve other than 'I don't have a full spellbook'.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The problem is more like, &quot;i only have 1 out of 4 of the big 60 nukes and can therefore only hit one resist type as a lvl 60 wizard, any other resist type and it's nearly as effective to drag along someone who's leveling up at raptors as it is to have me there.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The simplest way to resolve what you are talking about would be to simply make SS drop a little bit more and leave the other 2 alone, so why wouldn't that work? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That'd be better than big fat nothing, but a quest would be much better, since part of the reason that sunstrike is not more available is that few guilds farm kunark anymore.  A quest gets around that problem, and makes sunstrike available to most wizards like ice spear is, which helps alleviate the resist type issue.<br>
<br>
As far as EER and GSS, i feel they were innappropriately placed and so should be moved to more appropriate mobs.  If you disagree, that's your right, but that's why i think those 2  should be more available, particularly EER since it rounds out the resist types. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2007<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/6/03 7:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GM response on GSS and EER</span><hr size=1> &gt;Cute, and your point is? Moonfire is nevertheless a very powerful spell for a class who's balance is based only partly on their nukes, and i'm comparing spells from Luclin with other spells from Luclin.<br>
