PoP spells are a different level range and a different expansion that handles spell drops in a much more equitable manner.  The availablity of those spells is pretty well balanced compared to each other, with the glaring exception of a 2K vendor nuke for a different class, only one level above GSS, that was clearly balanced off GSS if you examine it.  Yet GSS is exceedingly rare, and in order to be balanced that needs to be addressed.  As i said earlier, some people have good reasons for remaining lvl 60, and those people should be able to access those spells which balance us at 60, not be forced to level up to obtain a PoP spell instead.  The availabilty of the PoP spells is actually a good argument that there was a problem with spell access that they tried to correct.  They did a good job, but i think our previous spells need adjustment as well.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The reason it seems that it is so hard to get is exactly what you mentioned, nobody farms Kunark anymore.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Exactly, and this is the reason i don't think a small increase in drop rate will have any noticeable effect.  Even if it drops more often if no one is farming that content, there are no scrolls to trickledown.  That's why i think they should add a quest for it in the grand tradition of the ice comet quest.  Then every 60 wizard is basically guaranteed 2 resist types.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I feel the placement of both was fine after the initial change to EER. GSS is very good upgrade to SS<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I disagree that these were appropriately placed, as i asked earlier, does any other caster have a spell that only drops off Emp. Ssra?  I really think GSS is the only one, and that's a big clue that it was misplaced.  Moving it down one notch along with EER would only increase it's availability a bit, it's not equivalent to asking for those spells to be on a vendor.  But i feel that the full repertoire of the basic nukes should be reasonably available, and Emp Ssra only does not meet that criteria.<br>
